<span id="viii.vi.iii-p2"></span><span class="c9"><span
id="viii.vi.iii-p2.1"></span>In</span> Bower’s *History of the Popes*
(ed. Philadelphia, 1847), vol. i. p. 22, may be seen an interesting note
on the “Pontifical” of Bucherius, under the name of Pontianus.  It was
this bishop who is said to have condemned Origen.  He probably shared
the fate of Hippolytus in exile, and was martyred under Maximin the
Thracian.

